# Phase System

## No Hardcoded Enums

Phases are **not** enums. They are created generically per arena via [PhaseProvider].

## Main Phases

- Created per arena by [PhaseProvider.createPhases]
- Ordered by [priority]; Core advances sequentially (nextPhase = priority + 1)
- Typical sequence: Map Voting → Game Voting → In-Game Lobby → In-Game → Ending
- Each arena can have a custom phase configuration

## Game Loop Phases (In-Game Phase Only)

- Each [MicroGame] defines its own via [MicroGame.createGameLoop]
- Games may have one (e.g. TNT Run) or multiple (e.g. Spleef: "building", "fighting")
- [ArenaContext.currentGameLoopPhase] is non-null only when in In-Game phase
- Games advance via [ArenaContext.advanceToNextGameLoopPhase]

## Key Types

| Type | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [Phase] | Main phase interface (id, name, priority, start, stop) |
| [GameLoopPhase] | Game loop phase within In-Game (game-specific) |
| [PhaseProvider] | Creates phase list per arena |
| [PhaseId] / [GameLoopPhaseId] | Value class identifiers |

## Reference

Pattern: phases per arena (Multimap<ArenaId, Phase>), priority-based advancement, In-Game phase holds game-specific game loop phases.
